text: This wonderful Viking Compass Pendant came very quickly and I love it so much! It does come with a solid chain that is 20" long which fits right over my head, and as you can see the back is polished smooth and I will be able to get them engraved. Just a word to the wise the pendant is solid 925 Sterling, not the necklace, that is just an added bonus you get. Also, if you want to polish it do NOT use liquid or paste polish or it will take out the inking! I found this out on a couple of my rings I was wearing while cleaning other jewelry the other day. Please just use a jewelry polishing cloth and that will be enough. And if you plan on cleaning other jewelry with a liquid cleaner, keep it far away from it, I would take it off just to be sure. I wouldn't want to damage the dark ink as it looks so nice and aged this way! Artist... Thank you so much for your work, it is wonderful and you have a clear eye for beauty and excellence! title: Deep Blue Lapis — a Stately Silver Piece
text:
So, here's the deal. I looked up how to test if an item is real silver because when this beautiful deep blue lapis ring came in the mail, I was stunned at its size! From the pics on Amazon, I had no idea how stately this actual ring was.
The all-knowing Internet — said one simple test to see if something is real silver is to grab a magnet because real silver will not attract to the magnet. Precious metals— gold, silver, etc are pure and nonmagnetic. Other (cheap) metals will attract to a magnet— like my keys in the picture.
As you can see in the picture, no matter which side or area I placed near the magnet, it was not attracted to it! Why did I doubt the silver content of the metal? Because the 925 stamp inside the ring band is in 2 pt. type size! Please make the 925 stamp bigger—- be proud of your quality!
This ring is beautiful and bigger than I expected! It is a great value and beautiful for the price:)

title: Where Has this Been All My Life!?
text: The presentation of "Chill Out" Relaxation Blend Roll-On Essential Oil is brilliant! Once you open the package, you can see how much Maddie, the EO Crafter, truly cares about what she makes, how it looks, and YOU! Beautiful presentation, thoughtfully done! "Chill Out" is a phenomenal scent. I applied it to  my inner wrists, my temples, and my lower neck (so the scent could waft up when I inhaled.) This is a great EO blend that melts into your skin beautifully with no mess after application. Some roller ball applicator bottles release far too much product, but this one does not. It allows you to apply the blended oil conservatively, assisting you in the need to apply without overdoing it. The scent is a soft, peaceful one; It does not assault you! Its perfect in strength, not cloying - but absolutely present and accounted for. I have severe anxiety disorder, and some days are fairly hard to get through. I'm not saying that "Chill Out" essential oil blend takes anxiety away. I can say that the scent dials down some of the feelings of tension, irritability, etc that I experience, and helps bring me back to a place that's more centered and calm. I wish that the scent was a little longer lasting, but this is truly not a deal-breaker! I will continue to buy this blend from Maddie. I like it enough that I want to have a bottle to keep in the house and another to keep in my handbag for assuring comfort when I'm out and about. Thank you, Maddie, for making such a terrific, quality product!

title: Naturally made, non-moisturizing soap bars with pleasing scents
text:
These soap bars come attractively wrapped and tied together. They are ready to give as a gift. Each bar is colored nicely. One is beige with speckles in it and the other has a swirl of green shades. I am not sure why these soap bars are named the way they are because they do not have the ingredients in them that their name indicates. One is named “Eucalyptus Aloe” and does not have any eucalyptus or aloe in it. The other bar is named “White Tea Mint” and does not have any white tea (or any other tea) or mint in it. Perhaps those are the scents that are supposed to be in the fragrance of each bar. Both bars have a good smelling fragrance and though they are not quite like their respective labels I think most people would find their scents pleasing. The bars are square shaped which makes them a little wider on one side than a regular bar of soap and harder to handle if you have small hands. But they can be cut in half with a knife so they can be handled easier. You have to use a sharp knife if you do cut them because they will crumble.
When bathing with these bars of soap, my SO complained that she did not like the smell of either bar, the soap left a film on her body and made her skin dry and stiff. While I liked the way both bars smelt they did dry out my skin rather than moisturizing it. I thought the 5 oils and the Shea butter in them would make my skin soft and moist but they didn't. I had to put on lotion after bathing. They may be good for someone who consistently has oily skin. title: Awesome High Quality Prints
text: These arts prints are simply awesome.  No two are the same, and they add such style and character to a wall.  I find they look perfect in Ribba frames from my local Ikea.  I've had a lot of people compliment on them and even order some for themselves after seeing the ones I purchased.  The print quality is much better than I originally expected (at the low price point) and I've yet to see any signs of poor ink use.  I'm not entirely sure if these really are actual pages from an old dictionary or if they are reproductions, but they look good enough to fool me.  I've ordered four of these (different styles) so far, and every one of them impresses me with the quality when I open it (they are shipped in a stiff envelope, in a box).  Only one of them has been printed slightly off "perfect center" but the design of the print was so that it wasn't even noticeable, almost even appeared to be the way it was meant to be. I look forward to all the new designs they come out with!
